This paper deals with a fundamental subroutine required by many approximation algorithms commonly adopted in industrial practice for large-scale search and learning. The paper proposes a new algorithm for computing multiple independent hashes of the data in constant time, which is likely to be of interest to researchers in data structures (cs.DS), information retrieval (cs.IR), machine learning (cs.LG), databases (cs.DB), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
